About gameplay, this year pass assistance changes

00:00:56.877 --> 00:01:00.597
It's not classic system anymore but a level system

00:01:00.597 --> 00:01:06.177
Level 1 is standard assist and level 2 and 3 helps the player to build his game

00:01:06.300 --> 00:01:12.540
and level "No", ...no logic i don't why it's called "no" is the Full Manuel configuration

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:16.320
Full manuel configuration will be explained in part 2 of this video

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:18.700
but for the moment look at this gameplay fluidity

00:01:18.820 --> 00:01:21.220
It's as good as Fifa Fluidity

00:01:21.340 --> 00:01:24.320
Players move in a real (finally) 360 Â° configuration

00:01:24.580 --> 00:01:27.200
the reactivity is impressive

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.920
and passes are easy but not too much

00:01:31.060 --> 00:01:35.380
well PES 2016's Gameplay is really (really) good

00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:38.520
Collision System

00:01:38.660 --> 00:01:43.580
Another major improvement in PES 2016 is the collision system

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.340
For a start it's really good, contacts are convincing

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:55.360
as you can see with Pirlo and look at Pogba's feet trying to take the ball away

00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:59.160
This is a real new feature which was missing in PES 2015

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:03.000
an other cool stuff, look at Totti chassing by Pirlo and Arturo Vidal,

00:02:03.080 --> 00:02:05.560
They never give up until they take the ball back

00:02:05.860 --> 00:02:06.360
A.I

00:02:08.260 --> 00:02:11.900
AI is a strong chapter in this preview

00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:16.140
I'v decided to talk about it even if i never play against the computer in PES

00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:19.760
