00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:28.640
I'v been able to orientate the game to the left wing

00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:34.120
and quickly, you can see all three defensive lines with Matuidi, Schneiderlin and Sakho

00:02:34.220 --> 00:02:38.700
All three defenders will follow the game action closely and nearly at the same time

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:43.020
Comparing with what i saw last year on PES 2015, there is a huge improvement

00:02:43.140 --> 00:02:47.080
with defenders reaction, and even in the way the computer built his game

00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:49.960
Computer has a better rythm, they dribble

00:02:50.140 --> 00:02:52.780
They don't hesitate to attack the ball keeper

00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:55.780
It's sometimes nearly as good as playing against a human player

00:02:55.867 --> 00:02:59.287
it's quite impressive at the beginning

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:02.480
to be honest it's more a huge improvement than a real revolution

00:03:02.540 --> 00:03:06.980
but i wanted to say that because Konami did  a good job with computer's reactions in superstar level

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:10.100
Look again at Pogba sliding tackle

00:03:10.140 --> 00:03:12.500
this for example i didn't see it coming

00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:14.800
